# ğŸ§  2. Core Design Principles (Universal)

These are **mental laws**, not stylistic rules.  
They apply to every design style the system generates.

### 2.1 Clarity  
Information must be understandable at a glance.

### 2.2 Hierarchy  
Guide attention with size, spacing, contrast, and position.

### 2.3 Emotional Resonance  
Aesthetics must match the emotional intention of the brand.

### 2.4 Accessibility  
Meet WCAG AA minimum, AAA when possible.

### 2.5 Consistency  
Tokens, spacing, and typography must form a coherent system.

### 2.6 Responsiveness  
Designs must adapt smoothly across screen sizes.

### 2.7 UX Psychology  
Use:
- Fittsâ€™s Law  
- Hickâ€™s Law  
- Gestalt principles  
- Affordances  
- Cognitive load theory  

### 2.8 Visual Harmony  
Balance whitespace, rhythm, alignment, proportions.

These principles guide Artoâ€™s and Stylistâ€™s thinking across all styles.

