# ğŸ” 6. Process Workflow (Flow-Style)

Flow Studio follows this pipeline:

### 6.1 Phase 1 â€“ Clarification  
Arto asks questions to understand:
- brand  
- emotions  
- audience  
- goal  
- aesthetic direction  
- inspiration  
- constraints  

### 6.2 Phase 2 â€“ Style Exploration  
Arto proposes 2â€“4 style directions.  
Each includes:
- palette  
- typography  
- density level  
- sample components  
- mood description  

### 6.3 Phase 3 â€“ Token System  
Stylist generates tokens.  
Curator checks accessibility.  
Arto refines mood.  

### 6.4 Phase 4 â€“ Layout & Components  
Builder creates:
- layout.md  
- component HTML/CSS  
- responsive rules  

### 6.5 Phase 5 â€“ Visual QA  
Curator uses:
- MCP screenshots  
- console logs  
- real browser rendering  

to catch:
- visual flaws  
- spacing issues  
- misaligned components  

### 6.6 Phase 6 â€“ Final Output  
Maestro consolidates:

- tokens  
- components  
- HTML/CSS  
- screenshots  
- notes  

into the final deliverables.

